From bad experiences and other perpectives, engineering mathematics should add another domain in to numbers:- what we call 'communication numbers' (or communication domain)$\in$T. T represents n$\ge$2.  
let there be n (n$>$0) clients for a data source included in (clients i.e. it to be counted in n) and link bandwidth 1.
\begin{enumerate}
\item when n=1 the data source can send data with (1/1)*bandwidth. This is not communication by definition. The source/client sends data to the source/client.
\item when n=2 the data source can send data with 1/2-1;
\item when n$>$ 2 the data source can send data with (1/n-1)*bandwidth;
\item when the data sources increase (n-data sources), the receiver receives data with (1/n-1)/n= (n/(n-1))
\end{enumerate}
Thus we prove T$\in$N is an existing set of domain.$\therefore$T subdomain of N (natural numbers n$\ge$1) is Telecommunications number.- not to confuse it with C complex numbers.\\
